---
title: Garlic Confit
servings: 4
tags: [condiment, garlic, oven, confit]
prep time: 5 minutes
cook time: 45 minutes
---

-- Preheat oven to 300°F.

Place @garlic{2%heads}(cloves separated and peeled) in a small baking dish or oven-safe vessel. Cover completely with @olive oil{}. Add @salt{}(optional) and @red pepper flakes{}(optional) to taste.

Roast at 300°F for ~{30-60%minutes} until cloves are completely tender and lightly golden.

-- Store covered in the oil in the refrigerator.
